cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DC, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the migration of a multi-terabyte astronomical archive from an object-oriented database to a relational database. This involves technical issues related to data organization, query support, and data mining performance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) due to the focus on data mining and search capabilities. Additionally, the paper touches on issues related to hardware performance and vendor support, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
